## Mandatory Rules

MANDATORY: Read the files in `.claude/rules/` before any implementation:

- `.claude/rules/tdd-enforcement.md` - RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle required
- `.claude/rules/best-practices.md` - Conventions and project standards
- `.claude/rules/architecture-boundaries.md` - Layer separation and responsibilities
- `.claude/rules/minimal-changes.md` - Narrow scope of changes
- `.claude/rules/security.md` - Security and sanitization (injection, XSS, secrets)
- `.claude/rules/commits-cicd.md` - Conventional Commits and CI priority

## Rule Document Maintenance

This file (CLAUDE.md) and the files in `.claude/rules/` are living documents. Keep them updated:

- **CLAUDE.md**: Update whenever the stack, commands, or project structure changes. This file is the entry point — if outdated, all derived instructions are compromised.
- **When to update**: When adding/removing dependencies, changing directory structure, build/test/lint commands, or project conventions.
- **Rules in `.claude/rules/`**: Review at the end of each development cycle. Remove rules that no longer apply and add new ones as the project evolves.
- **Principle**: Outdated rules are worse than no rules — they produce contradictory instructions and confuse the agent.
